<br>
Solution: Make NPCs ignore pets in the distance based awareness agro code. All other forms of getting agro like spells, damage, mobs assiting each other would stay the same. <br>
<br>
Has this been suggested before and if so was there any response from Verant? It would seem a decent solution to a major problem that doesn't require all that much work and doesn't give much more benefit above that needed to solve the problem.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/urhionsligo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>rhionsligo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 510<br> <font color=#333333>(5/4/02 7:30:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=194.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.lehigh.edu/~dsf3/EQ/starofdavid.gif width=36 height=37></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Making pets viable on raids and in hard areas - an idea</span><hr size=1> What you are describing has the same effect as putting pets on betaneutral faction.  It has been discussed in great length and there has been no word from verant on the issue other than the acknowledgement that the idea exists. <p><img src="http://www.lehigh.edu/~dsf3/EQ/rhionsligo.jpg" align="center"><br>
